//Recursive function to calculate factorial


Write a recursive function to find factorial of a given number.
The function accepts an integer parameter n.
The function returns the factorial of the number n.
The function returns 0 for a negative or 0 input.
/*
 * The calculateFactorial function accepts a single integer n as input and returns the factorial
 * It calculates factorial using a recursive algorithm
 * It finally returns the recursively calculated factorial
 * It returns 0 for invalid input (0 and -ve number)
 * Iteration   : factorial(n) = n * factorial(n-1).
 * Termination : fatorial(1) = 1.
 */
int calculateFactorial(int n)
{

if(n<=0) return 0;
if(n==1) return 1;
else return calculateFactorial(n-1)*n;

}
 
